      "evidence": "All protected API endpoints return 401 without valid JWT. Tested 6 scenarios: (1) GET /api/admin/users without auth -> 401 Not authenticated, (2) POST /api/admin/users without auth -> 401 Not authenticated, (3) GET /api/admin/users/some-id without auth -> 401 Not authenticated, (4) GET /api/admin/users with garbage JWT -> 401 Invalid or expired token, (5) GET /api/admin/users with malformed auth header -> 401 Not authenticated, (6) POST /api/admin/users with garbage JWT -> 401 Invalid or expired token. Health endpoint confirmed accessible at 200.",
